Remove the VERSION file to fix Windows builds.
On case-insensitive filesystems (Windows), MSVC resolves #include <version>
(a C++17/20 standard header) to this data file instead of the real standard
header, because Bazel adds the repo root to the include search path. The
preprocessor reads "0.3.1" as C++ source and fails with error C2059.
See https://github.com/BYVoid/OpenCC/pull/1084

--- VERSION
+++ /dev/null
@@ -1 +0,0 @@
-0.3.1
